Review.Titre: Shipping claims are inaccurate, restricted stock is misleading
Review.Contenu: Hello, your website states that orders received by 5 PM CST are shipped same day.  However, I'm in MST (Colorado) and tried to place an order around 3:15 PM, but your website had already defaulted to "Your order will ship the next business day".  Central time would be 4:15 PM.  I could not place an overnight order and had to look into alternate options.   Looking at your site today, I see a "Current warehouse time" that shows that you are not in the central time zone, but in the Eastern time zone. I saw that Newark had some stock, then found out when I tried to purchase the items, that they are not allowed to ship to my area. So between a distributor that has stock that cannot be sold to me, and a misleading website, my experience with Coilcraft was sub-standard.

Review.Titre: What's the point of having options, if you just decide for us!

To my surprise when I received the box from Coilcraft, there was a reel of 950 and then a strip of 50 pcs that was shoved into a cylinder container!  Really Coilcraft?!?!?

The plastic box containing the parts was cheap; it doesn't latch closed.The Styrofoam molding within the plastic box, holding the parts, also seemed low budget. Check AVX and their Cap containers; they are much better.

The foam piece placed on top of the pieces was not adequate for the job. Otherwise, the pieces ordered shipped right away and I appreciate that Coilcraft is one of the few variable inductor component makers out there who realize that most people aren't made out of money.-Update-Alright, before everyone surrounds Coilcraft's factory with torches and pitchforks over this Developer's Kit thing, please wait!They contacted me and generously offered me a new kit. This is way above and beyond good customer service. Their high quality products are the most essential thing keeping me as a customer. The fact that they are a stand up group of folks is icing on the cake. Buy Coilcraft!

Still a small price to pay for the convenience, but the parts arrived packed much more securely (and expensively!) than they needed to be.  A JiffyBag® with 60 cents postage would have got the parts here as fast and a lot cheaper.  Having said that, keep up the good work, Coilcraft!

Review.Titre: Coilcraft's M302 "unicoil" 7/10mm tunable rf inductor kit
Review.Contenu: I ordered a Coilcraft's M302 kit of "unicoil" 7/10 mm tunable RF inductors for the purpose of being able to determine the best valued inductor while prototyping for a medium volume application. The kit contains a large number of inductors and the inductors work well, but the kit arrived with the inductors scattered in the case, and the case could be better arranged to allow easily finding the inductor you want to test. Coilcraft competes with Wurth in this space, and although I prefer Coilcraft's inductors, Wurth's packaging is more user friendly.After hearing about this, Coilcraft contacted me and quickly resolved the issue.
